      <group id="content" extype="content">
        <trans-unit id="101" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Specifies that a field can be missing from a serialization stream so that the <bpt id="p1">&lt;xref href="System.Runtime.Serialization.Formatters.Binary.BinaryFormatter"&gt;</bpt><ept id="p1">&lt;/xref&gt;</ept> and the <bpt id="p2">&lt;xref href="System.Runtime.Serialization.Formatters.Soap.SoapFormatter"&gt;</bpt><ept id="p2">&lt;/xref&gt;</ept> does not throw an exception.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="102" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" extradata="MT">
          <source>This attribute allows you to specify that new fields in a serializable type (a type to which the &lt;xref:System.SerializableAttribute&gt; is applied to) are ignored by the &lt;xref:System.Runtime.Serialization.Formatters.Binary.BinaryFormatter&gt; or the &lt;xref:System.Runtime.Serialization.Formatters.Soap.SoapFormatter&gt;.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="103" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" extradata="MT">
          <source>This enables version-tolerant serialization of types created for older versions of an application that serializes data.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="104" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" extradata="MT">
          <source>For example, when the formatters encounter a stream produced by a version that does not include the new fields, no exception is thrown, and the existing data on the older type is processed as normal.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="105" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Initializes a new instance of the <bpt id="p1">&lt;xref href="System.Runtime.Serialization.OptionalFieldAttribute"&gt;</bpt><ept id="p1">&lt;/xref&gt;</ept> class.</source>
        </trans-unit>
